{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Federal Office of Bundeswehr Equipment, Information Technology and In-Service Support |nativename = Bundesamt für Ausrüstung, Informationstechnik und Nutzung der Bundeswehr (BAAINBw) |logo = |logo_width = |seal = Wappen baainbw.svg |seal_width = 180 px |seal_caption = |picture = |picture_width = |picture_caption = |formed = 1 October 2012 |preceding1 = |preceding2 = <!-- up to |preceding6= --> |dissolved = |superseding1 = |superseding2 = <!-- up to |superseding6= --> |agency_type = Federal Office |jurisdiction = [[Government of Germany]] |headquarters = [[Koblenz]], [[Germany]] |coordinates = |motto = |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = [[Ursula von der Leyen]] |minister1_pfo = [[List of German defence ministers|Federal Minister of Defence]] |chief1_name = Harald Stein |chief1_position = President |chief2_name = |chief2_position = |parent_agency = [[Federal Ministry of Defence (Germany)|Federal Ministry of Defence]] |website = [http://www.baainbw.de/ www.baainbw.de] |footnotes = }} The '''Federal Office of Bundeswehr Equipment, Information Technology and In-Service Support''' (''Bundesamt für Ausrüstung, Informationstechnik und Nutzung der Bundeswehr''; ''BAAINBw'') is located in Koblenz, [[Rhineland-Palatinate]] and directly reports to the [[Federal Ministry of Defence (Germany)]] located in [[Bonn]] and [[Berlin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wirtschaftslexikon.gabler.de/Definition/bundesamt-fuer-ausruestung-informationstechnik-und-nutzung-der-bundeswehr-baainbw.html |title=Bundesamt für Ausrüstung, Informationstechnik und Nutzung der Bundeswehr (BAAINBw) - Gabler Wirtschaftslexikon |publisher=[[Springer Gabler]] |accessdate=2015-01-28}}</ref> It is assigned with the task of equipping the [[German Armed Forces]] (Bundeswehr) with modern weapon systems considering [[cost efficiency]] aspects. In doing so, it is responsible for developing, assessing and procuring [[weapon systems]]. It was founded in 2012 by merging both ''Bundesamt für Wehrtechnik und Beschaffung'' (''BWB'') and ''Bundesamt für Informationsmanagement und Informationstechnik'' (''BWI'') with the goal of producing [[synergies]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rhein-zeitung.de/region/lokales/koblenz_artikel,-BWB-verliert-seinen-Namen-_arid,366797.html#.VMj0-i7P6PU |title=BWB verliert seinen Namen - Rhein-Zeitung Koblenz - Rhein-Zeitung |publisher=Rhein-Zeitung |date=2012-01-17 |accessdate=2015-01-28}}</ref> Among others, the [[Bundeswehr Technical and Airworthiness Center for Aircraft]] is an important branch of the agency.
